Rating: 3
I agree with the cook from Ottawa. The longer you take to scramble the eggs, on the lowest possible heat, the creamier and yummier they are. I use free range eggs called 'Country Golden Yolks' which have a lot more flavor than the pale-yolk eggs we usually buy today. The Boursin cheese is delicious!

