Rating: 4
This recipe was awesome! I made it for Mother's Day brunch and everyone raved! I used a cheaper version of Boursin that was just a plain cheese spread and added my own herbs- worked great! Also, I did not make the butter sauce for the asparagus- I think it would have ruined the dish. The textures matched perfectly- I undercooked the asparagus a bit for a sturdier texture to stand up to the creamy eggs. Delicious!

Rating: 3
You can't go wrong with asparagus, yum! But scrambled eggs really should be made over low heat and for much longer than is recommended. It should take 25-30 minutes to scramble the eggs. They can be rubbery if you cook too fast.